alerts.description:
...MAXIMUM AFTERNOON HEAT INDICES BETWEEN 103 AND 106 DEGREES
WILL CONTINUE ACROSS SOUTHEAST TEXAS THROUGH THE WEEK...
THE COMBINATION OF AFTERNOON MIDDLE 90 AMBIENT TEMPERATURES IN
TANDEM WITH 70 DEGREE DEW POINTS WILL PRODUCE INLAND MAXIMUM HEAT
INDICES IN THE 103 TO 106 DEGREE RANGE...104 TO NEAR 108 DEGREES
OVER THE COASTAL REGIONS...FOR A COUPLE OF HOURS. HEAT INDICES
WILL BE HIGHER ALONG AND NEAR THE COAST DUE TO HIGHER MOISTURE.
DESPITE THE FACT THAT HEAT ADVISORY CRITERIA WILL NOT BE ACHIEVED,
FOLKS SHOULD STILL TAKE THE PROPER PRECAUTIONS TO AVOID HEAT
ILLNESS IF SPENDING ANY APPRECIABLE TIME OUTDOORS. THE TWO MAIN
COURSES OF ACTION ONE CAN TAKE TO AVOID HEAT EXHAUSTION OR HEAT
STROKE IS TO LIMIT STRENUOUS OUTDOOR ACTIVITY DURING THE LATE
MORNING THROUGH EARLY EVENING HOURS AND TO DRINK ALOT OF WATER.
PERSONS ENGAGING IN OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES ARE STRONGLY URGED TO DRINK
PLENTY OF WATER...WEAR LIGHT WEIGHT AND LIGHT COLORED CLOTHING...AND
TO TAKE FREQUENT BREAKS FROM THE HEAT. LIMIT STRENUOUS ACTIVITIES
AND STAY IN SHADED AREAS AS OFTEN AS POSSIBLE. YOUNG CHILDREN AND
PETS SHOULD NEVER BE LEFT UNATTENDED IN VEHICLES UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES
AS CAR INTERIORS CAN REACH LETHAL TEMPERATURES IN JUST A MATTER OF
MINUTES. ALSO...MAKE SURE THOSE THAT ARE OLDER AND THOSE THAT ARE
SICK ARE LIVING IN AIR CONDITIONED ENVIRONMENTS.
LISTEN TO NOAA WEATHER RADIO OR YOUR LOCAL MEDIA FOR THE LATEST UPDATES
CONCERNING THIS ONGOING EARLY JULY HEAT WAVE.
